parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering assist can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the power steering assist warning message is displayed
the vehicle loses power steering functionality
the steering wheel vibrates uncontrollably
the vehicle is hard to maneuver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque sensor can cause the power steering assist to malfunction, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The power steering assist warning message is displayed
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle loses power steering functionality
the torque sensor needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering control module can cause the power steering assist to malfunction, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates to accelerate
the transmission warning indicator illuminates
the vehicle loses power
the RPMs race erratically
the vehicle will not shift into gear
the vehicle stalls
and the wrench icon appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the powertrain can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid propulsion system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The warning light chimes and displays "Safely Stop Vehicle"
the vehicle no longer accelerates and slows to a stop
and the hybrid system overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HCU can cause the brake pedal to travel to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop
the ABS light and brake light come on
and the message "Regen Brakes Disabled" appears on the dashboard.
